*Card image (thumbnail)

Use a single strong hero image — logo, screenshot, or cover art
Landscape/16:9 crops best given your aspect ratio constraint
Even a solid color graphic with text beats a missing image

*Short description (the desc field)

1–2 sentences max, visible on the card
Lead with what it is, follow with why it matters
Example: "SQL reporting system built for retail ops. Reduced weekly reporting time by 60%."

*Full log (the detail field)

This is your expandable modal content — go deeper here
Good sections: What it is → Tools/stack used → Outcome or status
HTML is supported so you can use <b> headers and line breaks

*Links

Always include at least one — live demo, GitHub, Instagram, video, anything
Dead-end cards with no link feel unfinished

*Category discipline

One card = one primary category. Don't try to fit a project into two places — pick the dominant context
PERSONAL entries can be looser/more casual in tone than CAREER ones
